class Solution {
    public long maximumSubarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        long ans = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        long sum = 0;
        Map<Integer, Long> minS = new HashMap<>();
        for (int x : nums) {
            long s1 = sum - x;
            long s2 = minS.getOrDefault(x + k, Long.MAX_VALUE / 2);
            ans = Math.max(ans, sum + x - Math.min(s1, s2));
            minS.merge(x, sum, Math::min);
            sum += x;
        }
        return ans > Long.MIN_VALUE / 4 ? ans : 0;
    }
}
The code is using a prefix sum and a hash map to store the minimum prefix sum for each element. The maximum sum of a good subarray of nums is the maximum of the current sum and the previous sum. The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of nums.

