class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0; // 操作次数
            int and = -1; // -1 的二进制全为 1
            for (int x : nums) {
                and &= x & mask;
                if (and != 0) {
                    cnt++; // 合并 x，操作次数加一
                } else {
                    and = -1; // 准备合并下一段
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= mask; // 答案的这个比特位必须是 1
                mask ^= 1 << b; // 后面不考虑这个比特位
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

The completed code uses bit manipulation to solve the problem. It first initializes the mask to 0 and the answer to 0. It then iterates over each bit position from the most significant bit to the least significant bit. For each bit position, it calculates the number of operations needed to make the bit position of all numbers in nums to be 0. If the number of operations is larger than k, it means we cannot make all numbers in nums have 0 in the current bit position. So we set the bit position in the answer to be 1 and exclude the current bit position from the mask. Finally, we return the answer.

